**Location:** Proof of Lemma 2.4, the step "as $q^\perp_{\Gamma(\cap_i\mathcal G_i)}=\bigvee_i q^\perp_{\Gamma(\mathcal G_i)}$ (by Corollary 2.3)".

Corollary 2.2 ($[q_1,q_2]=0$, $q_1q_2=q$) and Corollary 2.3 are proved only for **two** subgraphs. The application to a family $\{\mathcal G_i\}_{i=1}^s$ requires:
- pairwise commutation of all $q_{\mathcal G_i}$;
- $\prod_i q_{\mathcal G_i}=\bigwedge_i q_{\mathcal G_i}=q_{\cap_i\mathcal G_i}$;
- hence by de Morgan $q^\perp_{\cap_i\mathcal G_i}=\bigvee_i q^\perp_{\mathcal G_i}$.

This is an induction that uses the fact that $N=\Gamma(\mathcal G_1\cap\mathcal G_2)$ is **itself a graph product**, so Cor. 2.2 reapplies to $(\mathcal G_1\cap\mathcal G_2)$ vs $\mathcal G_3$, etc. Associativity of $\cap$ on the projection side must also be checked. None of this induction is carried out in the text.
